### Responsive Flexbox

Create layouts that adapt to screen size using flexbox.

---

### 1. Fluid Grid with Flex-Wrap

```css
.card-grid {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 20px;
}

.card {
  flex: 1 1 300px;
  /* Grows, shrinks, starts at 300px */
}
```

When container is wide: multiple cards per row.
When narrow: cards stack vertically.

---

### 2. Sidebar + Content Layout

```css
.layout {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.sidebar {
  flex: 1 1 250px;  /* Min 250px */
}

.main {
  flex: 3 1 500px;  /* 3x the space, min 500px */
}
```

---

### 3. Navigation Bar

```css
.nav {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 10px;
}

.nav-links {
  display: flex;
  gap: 20px;
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .nav-links {
    flex-direction: column;
    width: 100%;
  }
}
```

---

### 4. Holy Grail Layout

```css
body {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  min-height: 100vh;
}

.content {
  display: flex;
  flex: 1;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.content main {
  flex: 1 1 300px;
}

.content aside {
  flex: 0 0 200px;
}
```

---

### 5. Media Queries with Flex

```css
.gallery {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 15px;
}

.gallery img {
  flex: 1 1 200px;
  object-fit: cover;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .gallery img {
    flex: 1 1 150px;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .gallery img {
    flex: 1 1 100%;
  }
}
```

> **Key Pattern:** `flex: 1 1 minSize` with `flex-wrap: wrap` creates responsive layouts without media queries.
